translated: Österdahl, Georg, captain, director, Gothenburg, b. 1/9/90 in Örebro to organ-builder A. Ö. and Augusta Pettersson. — High school graduate in Stockholm in 1909, HHS 1913-1914. Employed at Clarholm & Bergman in Gothenburg from 1920, became a co-owner in 1925, and executive director after the company's assignment to A-B in 1930. Also executive director at Biläg. Verkst. A-B since 1922, Iwar Janson Kolonialvaru A-B since 1932, Benlock A-B since 1934, and Nya Hand. A-B Carl Arfvidson in Vara since 1942. Chairman of the management board for A-B Kemiifa, A-B Folkbilar, Swedish Wholesale Association, Grand-Ducal Import Authority, and Investigative Institute from 1941 to 1945. Also chairman of Swedish colonial goods wholesale national association, Gothenburg Wholesale Association, board member of Gothenburg Free Port A-B, and Gothenburg Merchant Association, Gothenburg Flour Industry Association, Western Sweden Sugar Wholesale Association, Swedish Colonial Goods Import Association, A-B Swedish ColonialgTOss., A-B Godsemottagning, International Chamber of Commerce, and president of International Colonial Goods Association. Member of the board for St. Jörgens hospital, chairman of the board for Gothenburg lyre theater. Recipient of the Royal Order of the North Star (RNO) and Royal Order of Vasa (RVO).
